title: Akaroa, Tide Predictions, 2017
description:
Akaroa, Tide Predictions, 2017. 

Tables are provided in both PDF and comma delimited text (CSV) format, and display the daily times and levels of high and low tides, for a particular location.

Use the PDF files if you want to print the tide tables, and the CSV files if you wish to import the data into another programme. 

The tide predictions on this website are not official tide tables as specified in Maritime Rules Part 25 Nautical Charts and Publications (pursuant to Section 36 of the Maritime Transport Act 1994).

LINZ accepts no liability for any direct, indirect, consequential or incidental damages that result from any errors in the information, whether due to LINZ or a third party, or that arise from the use, or misuse, of the information available from this site.

For more information see https://www.linz.govt.nz/sea/tides/tide-predictions/tide-prediction-formats

title: Auckland, Sea Level Data 2009
description:
Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. 

The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.

The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

description:
Leigh, Tide Predictions, 2022. 

Tables are provided in both PDF and comma delimited text (CSV) format, and display the daily times and levels of high and low tides, for a particular location.

Use the PDF files if you want to print the tide tables, and the CSV files if you wish to import the data into another programme.

title: Lottin Point, Sea Level Data 2008
description:
Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. 

The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.

The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.

The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

title: Napier, Tide Predictions, 2017
description:
Napier, Tide Predictions, 2017. 

Tables are provided in both PDF and comma delimited text (CSV) format, and display the daily times and levels of high and low tides, for a particular location.

Use the PDF files if you want to print the tide tables, and the CSV files if you wish to import the data into another programme. 

The tide predictions on this website are not official tide tables as specified in Maritime Rules Part 25 Nautical Charts and Publications (pursuant to Section 36 of the Maritime Transport Act 1994).

LINZ accepts no liability for any direct, indirect, consequential or incidental damages that result from any errors in the information, whether due to LINZ or a third party, or that arise from the use, or misuse, of the information available from this site.

description:
The New Zealand Nautical Almanac (NZ 204) is published annually by LINZ. It covers the period 1 July to 30 June and provides official information to aid safe navigation in New Zealand waters. The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.

The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

title: Oamaru, Tide Predictions, 2017
description:
Oamaru, Tide Predictions, 2017. 

Tables are provided in both PDF and comma delimited text (CSV) format, and display the daily times and levels of high and low tides, for a particular location.

Use the PDF files if you want to print the tide tables, and the CSV files if you wish to import the data into another programme. 

The tide predictions on this website are not official tide tables as specified in Maritime Rules Part 25 Nautical Charts and Publications (pursuant to Section 36 of the Maritime Transport Act 1994).

title: Port Chalmers, Sea Level Data 2010
description:
Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. 

The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.

The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

description:
Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. 

The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.

The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

title: Waiorua Bay, Tide Predictions, 2017
description:
Waiorua Bay, Tide Predictions, 2017. 

Tables are provided in both PDF and comma delimited text (CSV) format, and display the daily times and levels of high and low tides, for a particular location.

Use the PDF files if you want to print the tide tables, and the CSV files if you wish to import the data into another programme. 

The tide predictions on this website are not official tide tables as specified in Maritime Rules Part 25 Nautical Charts and Publications (pursuant to Section 36 of the Maritime Transport Act 1994).

LINZ accepts no liability for any direct, indirect, consequential or incidental damages that result from any errors in the information, whether due to LINZ or a third party, or that arise from the use, or misuse, of the information available from this site.

For more information see https://www.linz.govt.nz/sea/tides/tide-predictions/tide-prediction-formats

title: Wellington, Sea Level Data 2007
description:
Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. 

The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.

The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.
